            "open_state_content_bg": "#fefaff",
            "open_state_content_text": "#121212",
            "content": "<p>Step 1: Clean and dry the skin around the area.<br/>Step 2: Cut the patch to the size you need, leaving a small margin around the wound or pressure spot.<br/>Step 3: Remove the liner and smooth the bandage onto the skin without stretching it.<br/>Step 4: Replace when the edges lift, the seal is compromised, or the dressing turns white as it absorbs fluid.</p><p>Do not apply over infected, heavily bleeding, or very deep wounds without professional guidance.</p>",
