    "collapsible_content_nJrYmE": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_content_6w9ntk": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "What is a hydrocolloid bandage?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>It is a flexible wound dressing that absorbs light wound fluid and forms a protective gel-like environment over the area. This helps support wet healing while cushioning the skin from outside irritation.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_njkpDd": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Can I cut it to size?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. This patch is designed to be trimmed so you can fit smaller cuts, blisters, heels, toes, elbows, and other awkward areas more precisely.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_CVU4Bm": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Is it waterproof?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. Once applied to clean, dry skin, the dressing helps block outside moisture and stays on well during normal daily activity and showering.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_ETX7yr": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "How long should I leave one patch on?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Wear time depends on the area and how much fluid the wound releases. Replace it when the edges start lifting, the seal is no longer secure, or the patch turns white as it absorbs fluid.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_HTVjPX": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Can I use it for pressure sores?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>It can be used as a protective dressing for superficial pressure-prone areas, but open, severe, or worsening pressure ulcers should be assessed by a healthcare professional.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_Ahw39W": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Will it hurt when I remove it?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Most users find removal gentle. Peel it back slowly while supporting the surrounding skin. If needed, soften the adhesive with warm water first.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_z4rFdy": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "When should I avoid using it?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Do not use it on infected wounds, heavy bleeding, very deep wounds, or wounds that require professional medical treatment unless directed by a clinician.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        }
      },
